Allow WASI commands to inherit arbitrary Linux-style descriptors.

Brush represents persistent shell redirections as child fd mappings. Keep each
source owned until spawn, bound the mapping table, apply every dup before any
setup fd is closed, and never close a descriptor that is a final child target.

